The '''2011 Egyptian protests''' are a continuing series of street demonstrations taking place throughout Egypt from January 2010 onwards with organisers counting on the [[2010â2011 Tunisian protests|Tunisian uprising]] to inspire the crowds to mobilize. The demonstrations and riots were reported to have started over [[police brutality]], [[State of emergency|State of Emergency Laws]], [[unemployment]], the lack of housing, [[food inflation]], [[Political corruption|corruption]], [[freedom of speech]] and poor [[living conditions]]<ref name="Egypt braces for nationwide protests">{{cite web|author=Jailan Zayan |url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5hP30nA0bbEaHZKjlpUKhdHxoN8Cg?docId=CNG.95111380dfbe35f8a08d6124c5e915e8.71 |title=AFP â Egypt braces for nationwide protests |publisher=AFP |date=2011-01-25 |accessdate=2011-01-25}}</ref>.
